54struct yasm_section {
55 /*@reldef@*/ STAILQ_ENTRY(yasm_section) link;
56
57 /*@dependent@*/ yasm_object *object; /* Pointer to parent object */
58
59 /*@owned@*/ char *name; /* strdup()'ed name (given by user) */
60
61 /* associated data; NULL if none */
62 /*@null@*/ /*@only@*/ yasm__assoc_data *assoc_data;
63
64 unsigned long align; /* Section alignment */
65
66 unsigned long opt_flags; /* storage for optimizer flags */
67
68 int code; /* section contains code (instructions) */
69 int res_only; /* allow only resb family of bytecodes? */
70 int def; /* "default" section, e.g. not specified by
71 using section directive */
72
73 /* the bytecodes for the section's contents */
74 /*@reldef@*/ STAILQ_HEAD(yasm_bytecodehead, yasm_bytecode) bcs;
75
76 /* the relocations for the section */
77 /*@reldef@*/ STAILQ_HEAD(yasm_relochead, yasm_reloc) relocs;
78
79 void (*destroy_reloc) (/*@only@*/ void *reloc);
80};
81
82static void yasm_section_destroy(/*@only@*/ yasm_section *sect);

84/* Wrapper around directive for HAMT insertion */
85typedef struct yasm_directive_wrap {
86 const yasm_directive *directive;
87} yasm_directive_wrap;

93static void
94dir_extern(yasm_object *object, yasm_valparamhead *valparams,
95 yasm_valparamhead *objext_valparams, unsigned long line)
96{
97 yasm_valparam *vp = yasm_vps_first(valparams);
98 yasm_symrec *sym;
99 sym = yasm_symtab_declare(object->symtab, yasm_vp_id(vp), YASM_SYM_EXTERN,
100 line);
101 if (objext_valparams) {
102 yasm_valparamhead *vps = yasm_vps_create();
103 *vps = *objext_valparams; /* structure copy */
104 yasm_vps_initialize(objext_valparams); /* don't double-free */
105 yasm_symrec_set_objext_valparams(sym, vps);
106 }
107}
108
109static void
110dir_global(yasm_object *object, yasm_valparamhead *valparams,
111 yasm_valparamhead *objext_valparams, unsigned long line)
112{
113 yasm_valparam *vp = yasm_vps_first(valparams);
114 yasm_symrec *sym;
115 sym = yasm_symtab_declare(object->symtab, yasm_vp_id(vp), YASM_SYM_GLOBAL,
116 line);
117 if (objext_valparams) {
118 yasm_valparamhead *vps = yasm_vps_create();
119 *vps = *objext_valparams; /* structure copy */
120 yasm_vps_initialize(objext_valparams); /* don't double-free */
121 yasm_symrec_set_objext_valparams(sym, vps);
122 }
123}
124
125static void
126dir_common(yasm_object *object, yasm_valparamhead *valparams,
127 yasm_valparamhead *objext_valparams, unsigned long line)
128{
129 yasm_valparam *vp = yasm_vps_first(valparams);
130 yasm_valparam *vp2 = yasm_vps_next(vp);
131 yasm_expr *size = yasm_vp_expr(vp2, object->symtab, line);
132 yasm_symrec *sym;
133
134 if (!size) {
135 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX,
136 N_("no size specified in %s declaration"), "COMMON");
137 return;
138 }
139 sym = yasm_symtab_declare(object->symtab, yasm_vp_id(vp), YASM_SYM_COMMON,
140 line);
141 yasm_symrec_set_common_size(sym, size);
142 if (objext_valparams) {
143 yasm_valparamhead *vps = yasm_vps_create();
144 *vps = *objext_valparams; /* structure copy */
145 yasm_vps_initialize(objext_valparams); /* don't double-free */
146 yasm_symrec_set_objext_valparams(sym, vps);
147 }
148}
149
150static void
151dir_section(yasm_object *object, yasm_valparamhead *valparams,
152 yasm_valparamhead *objext_valparams, unsigned long line)
153{
154 yasm_section *new_section =
155 yasm_objfmt_section_switch(object, valparams, objext_valparams, line);
156 if (new_section)
157 object->cur_section = new_section;
158 else
159 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX,
160 N_("invalid argument to directive `%s'"), "SECTION");
161}
162
163static const yasm_directive object_directives[] = {
164 { ".extern", "gas", dir_extern, YASM_DIR_ID_REQUIRED },
165 { ".global", "gas", dir_global, YASM_DIR_ID_REQUIRED },
166 { ".globl", "gas", dir_global, YASM_DIR_ID_REQUIRED },
167 { "extern", "nasm", dir_extern, YASM_DIR_ID_REQUIRED },
168 { "global", "nasm", dir_global, YASM_DIR_ID_REQUIRED },
169 { "common", "nasm", dir_common, YASM_DIR_ID_REQUIRED },
170 { "section", "nasm", dir_section, YASM_DIR_ARG_REQUIRED },
171 { "segment", "nasm", dir_section, YASM_DIR_ARG_REQUIRED },
172 { NULL, NULL, NULL, 0 }
173};
174
175static void
176directive_level2_delete(/*@only@*/ void *data)
177{
178 yasm_xfree(data);
179}
180
181static void
182directive_level1_delete(/*@only@*/ void *data)
183{
184 HAMT_destroy(data, directive_level2_delete);
185}
186
187static void
188directives_add(yasm_object *object, /*@null@*/ const yasm_directive *dir)
189{
190 if (!dir)
191 return;
192
193 while (dir->name) {
194 HAMT *level2 = HAMT_search(object->directives, dir->parser);
195 int replace;
196 yasm_directive_wrap *wrap = yasm_xmalloc(sizeof(yasm_directive_wrap));
197
198 if (!level2) {
199 replace = 0;
200 level2 = HAMT_insert(object->directives, dir->parser,
201 HAMT_create(1, yasm_internal_error_),
202 &replace, directive_level1_delete);
203 }
204 replace = 0;
205 wrap->directive = dir;
206 HAMT_insert(level2, dir->name, wrap, &replace,
207 directive_level2_delete);
208 dir++;
209 }
210}

212/*@-compdestroy@*/
213yasm_object *
214yasm_object_create(const char *src_filename, const char *obj_filename,
215 /*@kept@*/ yasm_arch *arch,
216 const yasm_objfmt_module *objfmt_module,
217 const yasm_dbgfmt_module *dbgfmt_module)
218{
219 yasm_object *object = yasm_xmalloc(sizeof(yasm_object));
220 int matched, i;
221
222 object->src_filename = yasm__xstrdup(src_filename);
223 object->obj_filename = yasm__xstrdup(obj_filename);
224
225 /* No prefix/suffix */
226 object->global_prefix = yasm__xstrdup("");
227 object->global_suffix = yasm__xstrdup("");
228
229 /* Create empty symbol table */
230 object->symtab = yasm_symtab_create();
231
232 /* Initialize sections linked list */
233 STAILQ_INIT(&object->sections);
234
235 /* Create directives HAMT */
236 object->directives = HAMT_create(1, yasm_internal_error_);
237
238 /* Initialize the target architecture */
239 object->arch = arch;
240
241 /* Initialize things to NULL in case of error */
242 object->dbgfmt = NULL;
243
244 /* Initialize the object format */
245 object->objfmt = yasm_objfmt_create(objfmt_module, object);
246 if (!object->objfmt) {
247 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_GENERAL,
248 N_("object format `%s' does not support architecture `%s' machine `%s'"),
249 objfmt_module->keyword, ((yasm_arch_base *)arch)->module->keyword,
250 yasm_arch_get_machine(arch));
251 goto error;
252 }
253
254 /* Get a fresh copy of objfmt_module as it may have changed. */
255 objfmt_module = ((yasm_objfmt_base *)object->objfmt)->module;
256
257 /* Add an initial "default" section to object */
258 object->cur_section = yasm_objfmt_add_default_section(object);
259
260 /* Check to see if the requested debug format is in the allowed list
261 * for the active object format.
262 */
263 matched = 0;
264 for (i=0; objfmt_module->dbgfmt_keywords[i]; i++) {
265 if (yasm__strcasecmp(objfmt_module->dbgfmt_keywords[i],
266 dbgfmt_module->keyword) == 0) {
267 matched = 1;
268 break;
269 }
270 }
271
272 if (!matched) {
273 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_GENERAL,
274 N_("`%s' is not a valid debug format for object format `%s'"),
275 dbgfmt_module->keyword, objfmt_module->keyword);
276 goto error;
277 }
278
279 /* Initialize the debug format */
280 object->dbgfmt = yasm_dbgfmt_create(dbgfmt_module, object);
281 if (!object->dbgfmt) {
282 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_GENERAL,
283 N_("debug format `%s' does not work with object format `%s'"),
284 dbgfmt_module->keyword, objfmt_module->keyword);
285 goto error;
286 }
287
288 /* Add directives to HAMT. Note ordering here determines priority. */
289 directives_add(object,
290 ((yasm_objfmt_base *)object->objfmt)->module->directives);
291 directives_add(object,
292 ((yasm_dbgfmt_base *)object->dbgfmt)->module->directives);
293 directives_add(object,
294 ((yasm_arch_base *)object->arch)->module->directives);
295 directives_add(object, object_directives);
296
297 return object;
298
299error:
300 yasm_object_destroy(object);
301 return NULL;
302}
303/*@=compdestroy@*/
304
305/*@-onlytrans@*/
306yasm_section *
307yasm_object_get_general(yasm_object *object, const char *name,
308 unsigned long align, int code, int res_only,
309 int *isnew, unsigned long line)
310{
311 yasm_section *s;
312 yasm_bytecode *bc;
313
314 /* Search through current sections to see if we already have one with
315 * that name.
316 */
317 STAILQ_FOREACH(s, &object->sections, link) {
318 if (strcmp(s->name, name) == 0) {
319 *isnew = 0;
320 return s;
321 }
322 }
323
324 /* No: we have to allocate and create a new one. */
325
326 /* Okay, the name is valid; now allocate and initialize */
327 s = yasm_xcalloc(1, sizeof(yasm_section));
328 STAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&object->sections, s, link);
329
330 s->object = object;
331 s->name = yasm__xstrdup(name);
332 s->assoc_data = NULL;
333 s->align = align;
334
335 /* Initialize bytecodes with one empty bytecode (acts as "prior" for first
336 * real bytecode in section.
337 */
338 STAILQ_INIT(&s->bcs);
339 bc = yasm_bc_create_common(NULL, NULL, 0);
340 bc->section = s;
341 bc->offset = 0;
342 STAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&s->bcs, bc, link);
343
344 /* Initialize relocs */
345 STAILQ_INIT(&s->relocs);
346 s->destroy_reloc = NULL;
347
348 s->code = code;
349 s->res_only = res_only;
350 s->def = 0;
351
352 /* Initialize object format specific data */
353 yasm_objfmt_init_new_section(s, line);
354
355 *isnew = 1;
356 return s;
357}
358/*@=onlytrans@*/
359
360int
361yasm_object_directive(yasm_object *object, const char *name,
362 const char *parser, yasm_valparamhead *valparams,
363 yasm_valparamhead *objext_valparams,
364 unsigned long line)
365{
366 HAMT *level2;
367 yasm_directive_wrap *wrap;
368
369 level2 = HAMT_search(object->directives, parser);
370 if (!level2)
371 return 1;
372
373 wrap = HAMT_search(level2, name);
374 if (!wrap)
375 return 1;
376
377 yasm_call_directive(wrap->directive, object, valparams, objext_valparams,
378 line);
379 return 0;
380}

453void
454yasm_object_destroy(yasm_object *object)
455{
456 yasm_section *cur, *next;
457
458 /* Delete object format, debug format, and arch. This can be called
459 * due to an error in yasm_object_create(), so look out for NULLs.
460 */
461 if (object->objfmt)
462 yasm_objfmt_destroy(object->objfmt);
463 if (object->dbgfmt)
464 yasm_dbgfmt_destroy(object->dbgfmt);
465
466 /* Delete sections */
467 cur = STAILQ_FIRST(&object->sections);
468 while (cur) {
469 next = STAILQ_NEXT(cur, link);
470 yasm_section_destroy(cur);
471 cur = next;
472 }
473
474 /* Delete directives HAMT */
475 HAMT_destroy(object->directives, directive_level1_delete);
476
477 /* Delete prefix/suffix */
478 yasm_xfree(object->global_prefix);
479 yasm_xfree(object->global_suffix);
480
481 /* Delete associated filenames */
482 yasm_xfree(object->src_filename);
483 yasm_xfree(object->obj_filename);
484
485 /* Delete symbol table */
486 yasm_symtab_destroy(object->symtab);
487
488 /* Delete architecture */
489 if (object->arch)
490 yasm_arch_destroy(object->arch);
491
492 yasm_xfree(object);
493}

495void
496yasm_object_print(const yasm_object *object, FILE *f, int indent_level)
497{
498 yasm_section *cur;
499
500 /* Print symbol table */
501 fprintf(f, "%*sSymbol Table:\n", indent_level, "");
502 yasm_symtab_print(object->symtab, f, indent_level+1);
503
504 /* Print sections and bytecodes */
505 STAILQ_FOREACH(cur, &object->sections, link) {
506 fprintf(f, "%*sSection:\n", indent_level, "");
507 yasm_section_print(cur, f, indent_level+1, 1);
508 }
509}
510
511void
512yasm_object_finalize(yasm_object *object, yasm_errwarns *errwarns)
513{
514 yasm_section *sect;
515
516 /* Iterate through sections */
517 STAILQ_FOREACH(sect, &object->sections, link) {
518 yasm_bytecode *cur = STAILQ_FIRST(&sect->bcs);
519 yasm_bytecode *prev;
520
521 /* Skip our locally created empty bytecode first. */
522 prev = cur;
523 cur = STAILQ_NEXT(cur, link);
524
525 /* Iterate through the remainder, if any. */
526 while (cur) {
527 /* Finalize */
528 yasm_bc_finalize(cur, prev);
529 yasm_errwarn_propagate(errwarns, cur->line);
530 prev = cur;
531 cur = STAILQ_NEXT(cur, link);
532 }
533 }
534}

536int
537yasm_object_sections_traverse(yasm_object *object, /*@null@*/ void *d,
538 int (*func) (yasm_section *sect,
539 /*@null@*/ void *d))
540{
541 yasm_section *cur;
542
543 STAILQ_FOREACH(cur, &object->sections, link) {
544 int retval = func(cur, d);
545 if (retval != 0)
546 return retval;
547 }
548 return 0;
549}

558 if (strcmp(cur->name, name) == 0)
559 return cur;
560 }
561 return NULL;
562}

565void
566yasm_section_add_reloc(yasm_section *sect, yasm_reloc *reloc,
567 void (*destroy_func) (/*@only@*/ void *reloc))
568{
569 STAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&sect->relocs, reloc, link);
570 if (!destroy_func)
571 yasm_internal_error(N_("NULL destroy function given to add_reloc"));
572 else if (sect->destroy_reloc && destroy_func != sect->destroy_reloc)
573 yasm_internal_error(N_("different destroy function given to add_reloc"));
574 sect->destroy_reloc = destroy_func;
575}
576
577/*@null@*/ yasm_reloc *
578yasm_section_relocs_first(yasm_section *sect)
579{
580 return STAILQ_FIRST(&sect->relocs);
581}

583#undef yasm_section_reloc_next
584/*@null@*/ yasm_reloc *
585yasm_section_reloc_next(yasm_reloc *reloc)
586{
587 return STAILQ_NEXT(reloc, link);
588}

609
610yasm_bytecode *
611yasm_section_bcs_append(yasm_section *sect, yasm_bytecode *bc)
612{
613 if (bc) {
614 if (bc->callback) {
615 bc->section = sect; /* record parent section */
616 STAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&sect->bcs, bc, link);
617 return bc;
618 } else
619 yasm_xfree(bc);
620 }
621 return (yasm_bytecode *)NULL;
622}
623
624int
625yasm_section_bcs_traverse(yasm_section *sect,
626 /*@null@*/ yasm_errwarns *errwarns,
627 /*@null@*/ void *d,
628 int (*func) (yasm_bytecode *bc, /*@null@*/ void *d))
629{
630 yasm_bytecode *cur = STAILQ_FIRST(&sect->bcs);
631
632 /* Skip our locally created empty bytecode first. */
633 cur = STAILQ_NEXT(cur, link);
634
635 /* Iterate through the remainder, if any. */
636 while (cur) {
637 int retval = func(cur, d);
638 if (errwarns)
639 yasm_errwarn_propagate(errwarns, cur->line);
640 if (retval != 0)
641 return retval;
642 cur = STAILQ_NEXT(cur, link);
643 }
644 return 0;
645}

666static void
667yasm_section_destroy(yasm_section *sect)
668{
669 yasm_bytecode *cur, *next;
670 yasm_reloc *r_cur, *r_next;
671
672 if (!sect)
673 return;
674
675 yasm_xfree(sect->name);
676 yasm__assoc_data_destroy(sect->assoc_data);
677
678 /* Delete bytecodes */
679 cur = STAILQ_FIRST(&sect->bcs);
680 while (cur) {
681 next = STAILQ_NEXT(cur, link);
682 yasm_bc_destroy(cur);
683 cur = next;
684 }
685
686 /* Delete relocations */
687 r_cur = STAILQ_FIRST(&sect->relocs);
688 while (r_cur) {
689 r_next = STAILQ_NEXT(r_cur, link);
690 yasm_intnum_destroy(r_cur->addr);
691 sect->destroy_reloc(r_cur);
692 r_cur = r_next;
693 }
694
695 yasm_xfree(sect);
696}
697
698void
699yasm_section_print(const yasm_section *sect, FILE *f, int indent_level,
700 int print_bcs)
701{
702 if (!sect) {
703 fprintf(f, "%*s(none)\n", indent_level, "");
704 return;
705 }
706
707 fprintf(f, "%*sname=%s\n", indent_level, "", sect->name);
708
709 if (sect->assoc_data) {
710 fprintf(f, "%*sAssociated data:\n", indent_level, "");
711 yasm__assoc_data_print(sect->assoc_data, f, indent_level+1);
712 }
713
714 if (print_bcs) {
715 yasm_bytecode *cur;
716
717 fprintf(f, "%*sBytecodes:\n", indent_level, "");
718
719 STAILQ_FOREACH(cur, &sect->bcs, link) {
720 fprintf(f, "%*sNext Bytecode:\n", indent_level+1, "");
721 yasm_bc_print(cur, f, indent_level+2);
722 }
723 }

726/*
727 * Robertson (1977) optimizer
728 * Based (somewhat loosely) on the algorithm given in:
729 * MRC Technical Summary Report # 1779
730 * CODE GENERATION FOR SHORT/LONG ADDRESS MACHINES
731 * Edward L. Robertson
732 * Mathematics Research Center
733 * University of Wisconsin-Madison
734 * 610 Walnut Street
735 * Madison, Wisconsin 53706
736 * August 1977
737 *
738 * Key components of algorithm:
739 * - start assuming all short forms
740 * - build spans for short->long transition dependencies
741 * - if a long form is needed, walk the dependencies and update
742 * Major differences from Robertson's algorithm:
743 * - detection of cycles
744 * - any difference of two locations is allowed
745 * - handling of alignment/org gaps (offset setting)
746 * - handling of multiples
747 *
748 * Data structures:
749 * - Interval tree to store spans and associated data
750 * - Queues QA and QB
751 *
752 * Each span keeps track of:
753 * - Associated bytecode (bytecode that depends on the span length)
754 * - Active/inactive state (starts out active)
755 * - Sign (negative/positive; negative being "backwards" in address)
756 * - Current length in bytes
757 * - New length in bytes
758 * - Negative/Positive thresholds
759 * - Span ID (unique within each bytecode)
760 *
761 * How org and align and any other offset-based bytecodes are handled:
762 *
763 * Some portions are critical values that must not depend on any bytecode
764 * offset (either relative or absolute).
765 *
766 * All offset-setters (ORG and ALIGN) are put into a linked list in section
767 * order (e.g. increasing offset order). Each span keeps track of the next
768 * offset-setter following the span's associated bytecode.
769 *
770 * When a bytecode is expanded, the next offset-setter is examined. The
771 * offset-setter may be able to absorb the expansion (e.g. any offset
772 * following it would not change), or it may have to move forward (in the
773 * case of align) or error (in the case of org). If it has to move forward,
774 * following offset-setters must also be examined for absorption or moving
775 * forward. In either case, the ongoing offset is updated as well as the
776 * lengths of any spans dependent on the offset-setter.
777 *
778 * Alignment/ORG value is critical value.
779 * Cannot be combined with TIMES.
780 *
781 * How times is handled:
782 *
783 * TIMES: Handled separately from bytecode "raw" size. If not span-dependent,
784 * trivial (just multiplied in at any bytecode size increase). Span
785 * dependent times update on any change (span ID 0). If the resultant
786 * next bytecode offset would be less than the old next bytecode offset,
787 * error. Otherwise increase offset and update dependent spans.
788 *
789 * To reduce interval tree size, a first expansion pass is performed
790 * before the spans are added to the tree.
791 *
792 * Basic algorithm outline:
793 *
794 * 1. Initialization:
795 * a. Number bytecodes sequentially (via bc_index) and calculate offsets
796 * of all bytecodes assuming minimum length, building a list of all
797 * dependent spans as we go.
798 * "minimum" here means absolute minimum:
799 * - align/org (offset-based) bumps offset as normal
800 * - times values (with span-dependent values) assumed to be 0
801 * b. Iterate over spans. Set span length based on bytecode offsets
802 * determined in 1a. If span is "certainly" long because the span
803 * is an absolute reference to another section (or external) or the
804 * distance calculated based on the minimum length is greater than the
805 * span's threshold, expand the span's bytecode, and if no further
806 * expansion can result, mark span as inactive.
807 * c. Iterate over bytecodes to update all bytecode offsets based on new
808 * (expanded) lengths calculated in 1b.
809 * d. Iterate over active spans. Add span to interval tree. Update span's
810 * length based on new bytecode offsets determined in 1c. If span's
811 * length exceeds long threshold, add that span to Q.
812 * 2. Main loop:
813 * While Q not empty:
814 * Expand BC dependent on span at head of Q (and remove span from Q).
815 * Update span:
816 * If BC no longer dependent on span, mark span as inactive.
817 * If BC has new thresholds for span, update span.
818 * If BC increased in size, for each active span that contains BC:
819 * Increase span length by difference between short and long BC length.
820 * If span exceeds long threshold (or is flagged to recalculate on any
821 * change), add it to tail of Q.
822 * 3. Final pass over bytecodes to generate final offsets.
823 */
824
825typedef struct yasm_span yasm_span;
826
827typedef struct yasm_offset_setter {
828 /* Linked list in section order (e.g. offset order) */
829 /*@reldef@*/ STAILQ_ENTRY(yasm_offset_setter) link;
830
831 /*@dependent@*/ yasm_bytecode *bc;
832
833 unsigned long cur_val, new_val;
834 unsigned long thres;
835} yasm_offset_setter;
836
837typedef struct yasm_span_term {
838 yasm_bytecode *precbc, *precbc2;
839 yasm_span *span; /* span this term is a member of */
840 long cur_val, new_val;
841 unsigned int subst;
842} yasm_span_term;
843
844struct yasm_span {
845 /*@reldef@*/ TAILQ_ENTRY(yasm_span) link; /* for allocation tracking */
846 /*@reldef@*/ STAILQ_ENTRY(yasm_span) linkq; /* for Q */
847
848 /*@dependent@*/ yasm_bytecode *bc;
849
850 yasm_value depval;
851
852 /* span term for relative portion of value */
853 yasm_span_term *rel_term;
854 /* span terms in absolute portion of value */
855 yasm_span_term *terms;
856 yasm_expr__item *items;
857 unsigned int num_terms;
858
859 long cur_val;
860 long new_val;
861
862 long neg_thres;
863 long pos_thres;
864
865 int id;
866
867 int active;
868
869 /* NULL-terminated array of spans that led to this span. Used only for
870 * checking for circular references (cycles) with id=0 spans.
871 */
872 yasm_span **backtrace;
873 int backtrace_size;
874
875 /* First offset setter following this span's bytecode */
876 yasm_offset_setter *os;
877};
878
879typedef struct optimize_data {
880 /*@reldef@*/ TAILQ_HEAD(yasm_span_head, yasm_span) spans;
881 /*@reldef@*/ STAILQ_HEAD(yasm_span_shead, yasm_span) QA, QB;
882 /*@only@*/ IntervalTree *itree;
883 /*@reldef@*/ STAILQ_HEAD(offset_setters_head, yasm_offset_setter)
884 offset_setters;
885 long len_diff; /* used only for optimize_term_expand */
886 yasm_span *span; /* used only for check_cycle */
887 yasm_offset_setter *os;
888} optimize_data;
889
890static yasm_span *
891create_span(yasm_bytecode *bc, int id, /*@null@*/ const yasm_value *value,
892 long neg_thres, long pos_thres, yasm_offset_setter *os)
893{
894 yasm_span *span = yasm_xmalloc(sizeof(yasm_span));
895
896 span->bc = bc;
897 if (value)
898 yasm_value_init_copy(&span->depval, value);
899 else
900 yasm_value_initialize(&span->depval, NULL, 0);
901 span->rel_term = NULL;
902 span->terms = NULL;
903 span->items = NULL;
904 span->num_terms = 0;
905 span->cur_val = 0;
906 span->new_val = 0;
907 span->neg_thres = neg_thres;
908 span->pos_thres = pos_thres;
909 span->id = id;
910 span->active = 1;
911 span->backtrace = NULL;
912 span->backtrace_size = 0;
913 span->os = os;
914
915 return span;
916}
917
918static void
919optimize_add_span(void *add_span_data, yasm_bytecode *bc, int id,
920 const yasm_value *value, long neg_thres, long pos_thres)
921{
922 optimize_data *optd = (optimize_data *)add_span_data;
923 yasm_span *span;
924 span = create_span(bc, id, value, neg_thres, pos_thres, optd->os);
925 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&optd->spans, span, link);
926}
927
928static void
929add_span_term(unsigned int subst, yasm_bytecode *precbc,
930 yasm_bytecode *precbc2, void *d)
931{
932 yasm_span *span = d;
933 yasm_intnum *intn;
934
935 if (subst >= span->num_terms) {
936 /* Linear expansion since total number is essentially always small */
937 span->num_terms = subst+1;
938 span->terms = yasm_xrealloc(span->terms,
939 span->num_terms*sizeof(yasm_span_term));
940 }
941 span->terms[subst].precbc = precbc;
942 span->terms[subst].precbc2 = precbc2;
943 span->terms[subst].span = span;
944 span->terms[subst].subst = subst;
945
946 intn = yasm_calc_bc_dist(precbc, precbc2);
947 if (!intn)
948 yasm_internal_error(N_("could not calculate bc distance"));
949 span->terms[subst].cur_val = 0;
950 span->terms[subst].new_val = yasm_intnum_get_int(intn);
951 yasm_intnum_destroy(intn);
952}
953
954static void
955span_create_terms(yasm_span *span)
956{
957 unsigned int i;
958
959 /* Split out sym-sym terms in absolute portion of dependent value */
960 if (span->depval.abs) {
961 span->num_terms = yasm_expr__bc_dist_subst(&span->depval.abs, span,
962 add_span_term);
963 if (span->num_terms > 0) {
964 span->items = yasm_xmalloc(span->num_terms*sizeof(yasm_expr__item));
965 for (i=0; i<span->num_terms; i++) {
966 /* Create items with dummy value */
967 span->items[i].type = YASM_EXPR_INT;
968 span->items[i].data.intn = yasm_intnum_create_int(0);
969
970 /* Check for circular references */
971 if (span->id <= 0 &&
972 ((span->bc->bc_index > span->terms[i].precbc->bc_index &&
973 span->bc->bc_index <= span->terms[i].precbc2->bc_index) ||
974 (span->bc->bc_index > span->terms[i].precbc2->bc_index &&
975 span->bc->bc_index <= span->terms[i].precbc->bc_index)))
976 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_VALUE,
977 N_("circular reference detected"));
978 }
979 }
980 }
981
982 /* Create term for relative portion of dependent value */
983 if (span->depval.rel) {
984 yasm_bytecode *rel_precbc;
985 int sym_local;
986
987 sym_local = yasm_symrec_get_label(span->depval.rel, &rel_precbc);
988 if (span->depval.wrt || span->depval.seg_of || span->depval.section_rel
989 || !sym_local)
990 return; /* we can't handle SEG, WRT, or external symbols */
991 if (rel_precbc->section != span->bc->section)
992 return; /* not in this section */
993 if (!span->depval.curpos_rel)
994 return; /* not PC-relative */
995
996 span->rel_term = yasm_xmalloc(sizeof(yasm_span_term));
997 span->rel_term->precbc = NULL;
998 span->rel_term->precbc2 = rel_precbc;
999 span->rel_term->span = span;
1000 span->rel_term->subst = ~0U;
1001
1002 span->rel_term->cur_val = 0;
1003 span->rel_term->new_val = yasm_bc_next_offset(rel_precbc) -
1004 span->bc->offset;
1005 }
1006}
1007
1008/* Recalculate span value based on current span replacement values.
1009 * Returns 1 if span needs expansion (e.g. exceeded thresholds).
1010 */
1011static int
1012recalc_normal_span(yasm_span *span)
1013{
1014 span->new_val = 0;
1015
1016 if (span->depval.abs) {
1017 yasm_expr *abs_copy = yasm_expr_copy(span->depval.abs);
1018 /*@null@*/ /*@dependent@*/ yasm_intnum *num;
1019
1020 /* Update sym-sym terms and substitute back into expr */
1021 unsigned int i;
1022 for (i=0; i<span->num_terms; i++)
1023 yasm_intnum_set_int(span->items[i].data.intn,
1024 span->terms[i].new_val);
1025 yasm_expr__subst(abs_copy, span->num_terms, span->items);
1026 num = yasm_expr_get_intnum(&abs_copy, 0);
1027 if (num)
1028 span->new_val = yasm_intnum_get_int(num);
1029 else
1030 span->new_val = LONG_MAX; /* too complex; force to longest form */
1031 yasm_expr_destroy(abs_copy);
1032 }
1033
1034 if (span->rel_term) {
1035 if (span->new_val != LONG_MAX && span->rel_term->new_val != LONG_MAX)
1036 span->new_val += span->rel_term->new_val >> span->depval.rshift;
1037 else
1038 span->new_val = LONG_MAX; /* too complex; force to longest form */
1039 } else if (span->depval.rel)
1040 span->new_val = LONG_MAX; /* too complex; force to longest form */
1041
1042 if (span->new_val == LONG_MAX)
1043 span->active = 0;
1044
1045 /* If id<=0, flag update on any change */
1046 if (span->id <= 0)
1047 return (span->new_val != span->cur_val);
1048
1049 return (span->new_val < span->neg_thres
1050 || span->new_val > span->pos_thres);
1051}
1052
1053/* Updates all bytecode offsets. For offset-based bytecodes, calls expand
1054 * to determine new length.
1055 */
1056static int
1057update_all_bc_offsets(yasm_object *object, yasm_errwarns *errwarns)
1058{
1059 yasm_section *sect;
1060 int saw_error = 0;
1061
1062 STAILQ_FOREACH(sect, &object->sections, link) {
1063 unsigned long offset = 0;
1064
1065 yasm_bytecode *bc = STAILQ_FIRST(&sect->bcs);
1066 yasm_bytecode *prevbc;
1067
1068 /* Skip our locally created empty bytecode first. */
1069 prevbc = bc;
1070 bc = STAILQ_NEXT(bc, link);
1071
1072 /* Iterate through the remainder, if any. */
1073 while (bc) {
1074 if (bc->callback->special == YASM_BC_SPECIAL_OFFSET) {
1075 /* Recalculate/adjust len of offset-based bytecodes here */
1076 long neg_thres = 0;
1077 long pos_thres = (long)yasm_bc_next_offset(bc);
1078 int retval = yasm_bc_expand(bc, 1, 0,
1079 (long)yasm_bc_next_offset(prevbc),
1080 &neg_thres, &pos_thres);
1081 yasm_errwarn_propagate(errwarns, bc->line);
1082 if (retval < 0)
1083 saw_error = 1;
1084 }
1085 bc->offset = offset;
1086 offset += bc->len*bc->mult_int;
1087 prevbc = bc;
1088 bc = STAILQ_NEXT(bc, link);
1089 }
1090 }
1091 return saw_error;
1092}
1093
1094static void
1095span_destroy(/*@only@*/ yasm_span *span)
1096{
1097 unsigned int i;
1098
1099 yasm_value_delete(&span->depval);
1100 if (span->rel_term)
1101 yasm_xfree(span->rel_term);
1102 if (span->terms)
1103 yasm_xfree(span->terms);
1104 if (span->items) {
1105 for (i=0; i<span->num_terms; i++)
1106 yasm_intnum_destroy(span->items[i].data.intn);
1107 yasm_xfree(span->items);
1108 }
1109 if (span->backtrace)
1110 yasm_xfree(span->backtrace);
1111 yasm_xfree(span);
1112}
1113
1114static void
1115optimize_cleanup(optimize_data *optd)
1116{
1117 yasm_span *s1, *s2;
1118 yasm_offset_setter *os1, *os2;
1119
1120 IT_destroy(optd->itree);
1121
1122 s1 = TAILQ_FIRST(&optd->spans);
1123 while (s1) {
1124 s2 = TAILQ_NEXT(s1, link);
1125 span_destroy(s1);
1126 s1 = s2;
1127 }
1128
1129 os1 = STAILQ_FIRST(&optd->offset_setters);
1130 while (os1) {
1131 os2 = STAILQ_NEXT(os1, link);
1132 yasm_xfree(os1);
1133 os1 = os2;
1134 }
1135}
1136
1137static void
1138optimize_itree_add(IntervalTree *itree, yasm_span *span, yasm_span_term *term)
1139{
1140 long precbc_index, precbc2_index;
1141 unsigned long low, high;
1142
1143 /* Update term length */
1144 if (term->precbc)
1145 precbc_index = term->precbc->bc_index;
1146 else
1147 precbc_index = span->bc->bc_index-1;
1148
1149 if (term->precbc2)
1150 precbc2_index = term->precbc2->bc_index;
1151 else
1152 precbc2_index = span->bc->bc_index-1;
1153
1154 if (precbc_index < precbc2_index) {
1155 low = precbc_index+1;
1156 high = precbc2_index;
1157 } else if (precbc_index > precbc2_index) {
1158 low = precbc2_index+1;
1159 high = precbc_index;
1160 } else
1161 return; /* difference is same bc - always 0! */
1162
1163 IT_insert(itree, (long)low, (long)high, term);
1164}
1165
1166static void
1167check_cycle(IntervalTreeNode *node, void *d)
1168{
1169 optimize_data *optd = d;
1170 yasm_span_term *term = node->data;
1171 yasm_span *depspan = term->span;
1172 int i;
1173 int depspan_bt_alloc;
1174
1175 /* Only check for cycles in id=0 spans */
1176 if (depspan->id > 0)
1177 return;
1178
1179 /* Check for a circular reference by looking to see if this dependent
1180 * span is in our backtrace.
1181 */
1182 if (optd->span->backtrace) {
1183 for (i=0; i<optd->span->backtrace_size; i++) {
1184 if (optd->span->backtrace[i] == depspan)
1185 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_VALUE,
1186 N_("circular reference detected"));
1187 }
1188 }
1189
1190 /* Add our complete backtrace and ourselves to backtrace of dependent
1191 * span.
1192 */
1193 if (!depspan->backtrace) {
1194 depspan->backtrace = yasm_xmalloc((optd->span->backtrace_size+1)*
1195 sizeof(yasm_span *));
1196 if (optd->span->backtrace_size > 0)
1197 memcpy(depspan->backtrace, optd->span->backtrace,
1198 optd->span->backtrace_size*sizeof(yasm_span *));
1199 depspan->backtrace[optd->span->backtrace_size] = optd->span;
1200 depspan->backtrace_size = optd->span->backtrace_size+1;
1201 return;
1202 }
1203
1204 /* Add our complete backtrace, checking for duplicates */
1205 depspan_bt_alloc = depspan->backtrace_size;
1206 for (i=0; i<optd->span->backtrace_size; i++) {
1207 int present = 0;
1208 int j;
1209 for (j=0; j<depspan->backtrace_size; j++) {
1210 if (optd->span->backtrace[i] == optd->span->backtrace[j]) {
1211 present = 1;
1212 break;
1213 }
1214 }
1215 if (present)
1216 continue;
1217 /* Not already in array; add it. */
1218 if (depspan->backtrace_size >= depspan_bt_alloc)
1219 {
1220 depspan_bt_alloc *= 2;
1221 depspan->backtrace =
1222 yasm_xrealloc(depspan->backtrace,
1223 depspan_bt_alloc*sizeof(yasm_span *));
1224 }
1225 depspan->backtrace[depspan->backtrace_size] = optd->span->backtrace[i];
1226 depspan->backtrace_size++;
1227 }
1228
1229 /* Add ourselves. */
1230 if (depspan->backtrace_size >= depspan_bt_alloc)
1231 {
1232 depspan_bt_alloc++;
1233 depspan->backtrace =
1234 yasm_xrealloc(depspan->backtrace,
1235 depspan_bt_alloc*sizeof(yasm_span *));
1236 }
1237 depspan->backtrace[depspan->backtrace_size] = optd->span;
1238 depspan->backtrace_size++;
1239}
1240
1241static void
1242optimize_term_expand(IntervalTreeNode *node, void *d)
1243{
1244 optimize_data *optd = d;
1245 yasm_span_term *term = node->data;
1246 yasm_span *span = term->span;
1247 long len_diff = optd->len_diff;
1248 long precbc_index, precbc2_index;
1249
1250 /* Don't expand inactive spans */
1251 if (!span->active)
1252 return;
1253
1254 /* Update term length */
1255 if (term->precbc)
1256 precbc_index = term->precbc->bc_index;
1257 else
1258 precbc_index = span->bc->bc_index-1;
1259
1260 if (term->precbc2)
1261 precbc2_index = term->precbc2->bc_index;
1262 else
1263 precbc2_index = span->bc->bc_index-1;
1264
1265 if (precbc_index < precbc2_index)
1266 term->new_val += len_diff;
1267 else
1268 term->new_val -= len_diff;
1269
1270 /* If already on Q, don't re-add */
1271 if (span->active == 2)
1272 return;
1273
1274 /* Update term and check against thresholds */
1275 if (!recalc_normal_span(span))
1276 return; /* didn't exceed thresholds, we're done */
1277
1278 /* Exceeded thresholds, need to add to Q for expansion */
1279 if (span->id <= 0)
1280 STAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&optd->QA, span, linkq);
1281 else
1282 STAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&optd->QB, span, linkq);
1283 span->active = 2; /* Mark as being in Q */
1284}
1285
1286void
1287yasm_object_optimize(yasm_object *object, yasm_errwarns *errwarns)
1288{
1289 yasm_section *sect;
1290 unsigned long bc_index = 0;
1291 int saw_error = 0;
1292 optimize_data optd;
1293 yasm_span *span, *span_temp;
1294 yasm_offset_setter *os;
1295 int retval;
1296 unsigned int i;
1297
1298 TAILQ_INIT(&optd.spans);
1299 STAILQ_INIT(&optd.offset_setters);
1300 optd.itree = IT_create();
1301
1302 /* Create an placeholder offset setter for spans to point to; this will
1303 * get updated if/when we actually run into one.
1304 */
1305 os = yasm_xmalloc(sizeof(yasm_offset_setter));
1306 os->bc = NULL;
1307 os->cur_val = 0;
1308 os->new_val = 0;
1309 os->thres = 0;
1310 STAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&optd.offset_setters, os, link);
1311 optd.os = os;
1312
1313 /* Step 1a */
1314 STAILQ_FOREACH(sect, &object->sections, link) {
1315 unsigned long offset = 0;
1316
1317 yasm_bytecode *bc = STAILQ_FIRST(&sect->bcs);
1318
1319 bc->bc_index = bc_index++;
1320
1321 /* Skip our locally created empty bytecode first. */
1322 bc = STAILQ_NEXT(bc, link);
1323
1324 /* Iterate through the remainder, if any. */
1325 while (bc) {
1326 bc->bc_index = bc_index++;
1327 bc->offset = offset;
1328
1329 retval = yasm_bc_calc_len(bc, optimize_add_span, &optd);
1330 yasm_errwarn_propagate(errwarns, bc->line);
1331 if (retval)
1332 saw_error = 1;
1333 else {
1334 if (bc->callback->special == YASM_BC_SPECIAL_OFFSET) {
1335 /* Remember it as offset setter */
1336 os->bc = bc;
1337 os->thres = yasm_bc_next_offset(bc);
1338
1339 /* Create new placeholder */
1340 os = yasm_xmalloc(sizeof(yasm_offset_setter));
1341 os->bc = NULL;
1342 os->cur_val = 0;
1343 os->new_val = 0;
1344 os->thres = 0;
1345 STAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&optd.offset_setters, os, link);
1346 optd.os = os;
1347
1348 if (bc->multiple) {
1349 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_VALUE,
1350 N_("cannot combine multiples and setting assembly position"));
1351 yasm_errwarn_propagate(errwarns, bc->line);
1352 saw_error = 1;
1353 }
1354 }
1355
1356 offset += bc->len*bc->mult_int;
1357 }
1358
1359 bc = STAILQ_NEXT(bc, link);
1360 }
1361 }
1362
1363 if (saw_error) {
1364 optimize_cleanup(&optd);
1365 return;
1366 }
1367
1368 /* Step 1b */
1369 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(span, &optd.spans, link, span_temp) {
1370 span_create_terms(span);
1371 if (yasm_error_occurred()) {
1372 yasm_errwarn_propagate(errwarns, span->bc->line);
1373 saw_error = 1;
1374 } else if (recalc_normal_span(span)) {
1375 retval = yasm_bc_expand(span->bc, span->id, span->cur_val,
1376 span->new_val, &span->neg_thres,
1377 &span->pos_thres);
1378 yasm_errwarn_propagate(errwarns, span->bc->line);
1379 if (retval < 0)
1380 saw_error = 1;
1381 else if (retval > 0) {
1382 if (!span->active) {
1383 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_VALUE,
1384 N_("secondary expansion of an external/complex value"));
1385 yasm_errwarn_propagate(errwarns, span->bc->line);
1386 saw_error = 1;
1387 }
1388 } else {
1389 TAILQ_REMOVE(&optd.spans, span, link);
1390 span_destroy(span);
1391 continue;
1392 }
1393 }
1394 span->cur_val = span->new_val;
1395 }
1396
1397 if (saw_error) {
1398 optimize_cleanup(&optd);
1399 return;
1400 }
1401
1402 /* Step 1c */
1403 if (update_all_bc_offsets(object, errwarns)) {
1404 optimize_cleanup(&optd);
1405 return;
1406 }
1407
1408 /* Step 1d */
1409 STAILQ_INIT(&optd.QB);
1410 TAILQ_FOREACH(span, &optd.spans, link) {
1411 yasm_intnum *intn;
1412
1413 /* Update span terms based on new bc offsets */
1414 for (i=0; i<span->num_terms; i++) {
1415 intn = yasm_calc_bc_dist(span->terms[i].precbc,
1416 span->terms[i].precbc2);
1417 if (!intn)
1418 yasm_internal_error(N_("could not calculate bc distance"));
1419 span->terms[i].cur_val = span->terms[i].new_val;
1420 span->terms[i].new_val = yasm_intnum_get_int(intn);
1421 yasm_intnum_destroy(intn);
1422 }
1423 if (span->rel_term) {
1424 span->rel_term->cur_val = span->rel_term->new_val;
1425 if (span->rel_term->precbc2)
1426 span->rel_term->new_val =
1427 yasm_bc_next_offset(span->rel_term->precbc2) -
1428 span->bc->offset;
1429 else
1430 span->rel_term->new_val = span->bc->offset -
1431 yasm_bc_next_offset(span->rel_term->precbc);
1432 }
1433
1434 if (recalc_normal_span(span)) {
1435 /* Exceeded threshold, add span to QB */
1436 STAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&optd.QB, span, linkq);
1437 span->active = 2;
1438 }
1439 }
1440
1441 /* Do we need step 2? If not, go ahead and exit. */
1442 if (STAILQ_EMPTY(&optd.QB)) {
1443 optimize_cleanup(&optd);
1444 return;
1445 }
1446
1447 /* Update offset-setters values */
1448 STAILQ_FOREACH(os, &optd.offset_setters, link) {
1449 if (!os->bc)
1450 continue;
1451 os->thres = yasm_bc_next_offset(os->bc);
1452 os->new_val = os->bc->offset;
1453 os->cur_val = os->new_val;
1454 }
1455
1456 /* Build up interval tree */
1457 TAILQ_FOREACH(span, &optd.spans, link) {
1458 for (i=0; i<span->num_terms; i++)
1459 optimize_itree_add(optd.itree, span, &span->terms[i]);
1460 if (span->rel_term)
1461 optimize_itree_add(optd.itree, span, span->rel_term);
1462 }
1463
1464 /* Look for cycles in times expansion (span.id==0) */
1465 TAILQ_FOREACH(span, &optd.spans, link) {
1466 if (span->id > 0)
1467 continue;
1468 optd.span = span;
1469 IT_enumerate(optd.itree, (long)span->bc->bc_index,
1470 (long)span->bc->bc_index, &optd, check_cycle);
1471 if (yasm_error_occurred()) {
1472 yasm_errwarn_propagate(errwarns, span->bc->line);
1473 saw_error = 1;
1474 }
1475 }
1476
1477 if (saw_error) {
1478 optimize_cleanup(&optd);
1479 return;
1480 }
1481
1482 /* Step 2 */
1483 STAILQ_INIT(&optd.QA);
1484 while (!STAILQ_EMPTY(&optd.QA) || !(STAILQ_EMPTY(&optd.QB))) {
1485 unsigned long orig_len;
1486 long offset_diff;
1487
1488 /* QA is for TIMES, update those first, then update non-TIMES.
1489 * This is so that TIMES can absorb increases before we look at
1490 * expanding non-TIMES BCs.
1491 */
1492 if (!STAILQ_EMPTY(&optd.QA)) {
1493 span = STAILQ_FIRST(&optd.QA);
1494 STAILQ_REMOVE_HEAD(&optd.QA, linkq);
1495 } else {
1496 span = STAILQ_FIRST(&optd.QB);
1497 STAILQ_REMOVE_HEAD(&optd.QB, linkq);
1498 }
1499
1500 if (!span->active)
1501 continue;
1502 span->active = 1; /* no longer in Q */
1503
1504 /* Make sure we ended up ultimately exceeding thresholds; due to
1505 * offset BCs we may have been placed on Q and then reduced in size
1506 * again.
1507 */
1508 if (!recalc_normal_span(span))
1509 continue;
1510
1511 orig_len = span->bc->len * span->bc->mult_int;
1512
1513 retval = yasm_bc_expand(span->bc, span->id, span->cur_val,
1514 span->new_val, &span->neg_thres,
1515 &span->pos_thres);
1516 yasm_errwarn_propagate(errwarns, span->bc->line);
1517
1518 if (retval < 0) {
1519 /* error */
1520 saw_error = 1;
1521 continue;
1522 } else if (retval > 0) {
1523 /* another threshold, keep active */
1524 for (i=0; i<span->num_terms; i++)
1525 span->terms[i].cur_val = span->terms[i].new_val;
1526 if (span->rel_term)
1527 span->rel_term->cur_val = span->rel_term->new_val;
1528 span->cur_val = span->new_val;
1529 } else
1530 span->active = 0; /* we're done with this span */
1531
1532 optd.len_diff = span->bc->len * span->bc->mult_int - orig_len;
1533 if (optd.len_diff == 0)
1534 continue; /* didn't increase in size */
1535
1536 /* Iterate over all spans dependent across the bc just expanded */
1537 IT_enumerate(optd.itree, (long)span->bc->bc_index,
1538 (long)span->bc->bc_index, &optd, optimize_term_expand);
1539
1540 /* Iterate over offset-setters that follow the bc just expanded.
1541 * Stop iteration if:
1542 * - no more offset-setters in this section
1543 * - offset-setter didn't move its following offset
1544 */
1545 os = span->os;
1546 offset_diff = optd.len_diff;
1547 while (os->bc && os->bc->section == span->bc->section
1548 && offset_diff != 0) {
1549 unsigned long old_next_offset = os->cur_val + os->bc->len;
1550 long neg_thres_temp;
1551
1552 if (offset_diff < 0 && (unsigned long)(-offset_diff) > os->new_val)
1553 yasm_internal_error(N_("org/align went to negative offset"));
1554 os->new_val += offset_diff;
1555
1556 orig_len = os->bc->len;
1557 retval = yasm_bc_expand(os->bc, 1, (long)os->cur_val,
1558 (long)os->new_val, &neg_thres_temp,
1559 (long *)&os->thres);
1560 yasm_errwarn_propagate(errwarns, os->bc->line);
1561
1562 offset_diff = os->new_val + os->bc->len - old_next_offset;
1563 optd.len_diff = os->bc->len - orig_len;
1564 if (optd.len_diff != 0)
1565 IT_enumerate(optd.itree, (long)os->bc->bc_index,
1566 (long)os->bc->bc_index, &optd, optimize_term_expand);
1567
1568 os->cur_val = os->new_val;
1569 os = STAILQ_NEXT(os, link);
1570 }
1571 }
1572
1573 if (saw_error) {
1574 optimize_cleanup(&optd);
1575 return;
1576 }
1577
1578 /* Step 3 */
1579 update_all_bc_offsets(object, errwarns);
1580 optimize_cleanup(&optd);
1581}
